\series bold 
2-D Collisions Intelligent Guesses & Observations 
\layout Standard

Conservation of momentum can be used to solve a variety of collision and
 explosion problems.
 So far we have only considered momentum conservation in one dimension,
 but real collisions lead to motions in two and three dimensions.
 For example, air molecules are continually colliding in space and bouncing
 off in different directions.
 
\layout Standard

